JOHANNESBURG - Convicted racist Adam Catzavelos has apologised again to South Africans. He was back in the Randburg magistrate's court for sentencing proceedings. Court has adjourned until 28 February. READ: Adam Catzavelos has pleaded guilty to crimen injuria charge The Johannesburg businessman was charged in 2018 after a video of him using the k-word went viral. Later, he pleaded guilty to crimen injuria. He admitted that the k-word is hurtful and said he didn't intend to harm anyone. READ: Catzavelos reaches settlement with SAHRC In August last year, Catzavelos reached a settlement with the Human Rights Commission in a separate case. His lawyer Lawley Shain said his client wants to take responsibility for his actions.